THIS‼️‼️‼️‼️ Repost from @grassrootslaw
•
San Antonio Councilmember @theloserteacher has an important question that every city council should be asking: As we see increases in officers, have we seen a decrease in crime?⁠
⁠
The answer in San Antonio and many cities across this country is a resounding NO.⁠
⁠
We are so proud to have helped elect Jalen because he is fighting to address the root causes of crime and invest in our communities instead of thinking that hiring more and more police will somehow stop crime when it hasn't worked. Ever.⁠
⁠
After decades of mass incarceration and continually increasing police budgets, we need local leaders everywhere who will fight for real public safety beyond policing.
